Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.31, 9. The fabricant's name seems to have be short, not Aristokles, known to have worked in Eukrates' year, c.150 BC. There are several other possibilities.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1479)
